{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"18326","heading":"Development of technologies and in-space capabilities for beyond near-Earth space missions","label":"18326 Development of technologies and in-space capabilities for beyond near-Earth space missions","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/ch159/schII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18326","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextSection 905 of this Act, referred to in subsec. (d), is , , , which is not classified to the Code.Pub. L. 111–267, title IX, § 905124 Stat. 2836Oct. 11, 2010"],"amendments":["References in TextSection 905 of this Act, referred to in subsec. (d), is , , , which is not classified to the Code.Pub. L. 111–267, title IX, § 905124 Stat. 2836Oct. 11, 2010"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Development authorized","label":"a Development authorized","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18326%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18326%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Technologies identified as necessary elements of missions beyond low-Earth orbit.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18326%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In-space capabilities such as refueling and storage technology, orbital transfer stages, innovative in-space propulsion technology, communications, and data management that facilitate a broad range of users (including military and commercial) and applications defining the architecture and design of such missions.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18326%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Spacesuit development and associated life support technology.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/a/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18326%2Fa%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Flagship missions.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Investments","label":"b Investments","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18326%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18326%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"in space technologies such as advanced propulsion, propellant depots, in situ resource utilization, and robotic payloads or capabilities that enable human missions beyond low-Earth orbit ultimately leading to Mars;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18326%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18326%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to integrate with the Space Launch System and other space-based systems;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18326%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to provide opportunities for in-space servicing of and delivery to multiple space-based platforms; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18326%2Fb%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to facilitate international efforts to expand human presence to deep space destinations;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18326%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"in advanced life support technologies and capabilities;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18326%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"in technologies and capabilities relating to in-space power, propulsion, and energy systems;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18326%2Fb%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"in technologies and capabilities relating to in-space propellant transfer and storage;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18326%2Fb%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"in technologies and capabilities relating to in situ resource utilization; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":null,"label":"7","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18326%2Fb%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"in expanded research to understand the greatest biological impediments to human deep space missions, especially the radiation challenge.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Utilization of ISS as testbed","label":"c Utilization of ISS as testbed","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18326%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Administrator may utilize the ISS as a testbed for any technology or capability developed under subsection (a) in a manner consistent with the provisions of this chapter.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Coordination","label":"d Coordination","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s18326","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs18326%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Administrator shall coordinate development of technologies and capabilities under this section through an overall agency technology approach, as authorized by section 905 of this Act.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
